physical_examinations.vital_signs: Hematocrit: 22% initially; declined to as low as 28% when not taking iron supplementation. No other vital signs specified.
physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Enlarged, midline, but mobile firm pelvic mass on pelvic examination; ultrasound showed a uterus measuring 14 cm with multiple fibroids, the largest being 6.7 cm. Six months ago, a pelvic ultrasound assessed her uterus at 11.9 cm with multiple fibroids, largest at 5.2 cm.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Initially, symptoms resolved after myomectomy but returned about 1 year later, with heavy periods and fatigue reoccurring.
